snippet: The couple were on their way to the airport in Columbus, Miss., on Saturday when they were arrested by F.B.I. agents after unwittingly making travel plans with undercover federal agents on social media.
abstract: FBI agents arrest newlywed Mississippi couple Jaelyn Delshaun Young and Muhammad Oda Dakhlalla as they head to airport for trip to Syria to join Islamic State.
lead_paragraph: The couple were on their way to the airport in Columbus, Miss., on Saturday when they were arrested by F.B.I. agents after unwittingly making travel plans with undercover federal agents on social media.

headline.main: Newlyweds Are Accused of Planning to Join ISIS
